(357807, 11299, 357137, 'Fudgepacker', 15152, '', 1365983482, 'Just wanted to point out that SA only guns ie. 1911 can not second strike just by pulling the trigger. It''s hammer needs to be recocked (and technically a striker can also be reset without ejecting the round)... It''s not often that ED Bro isn''t right, but when it happens, you have to jump on it :)\n\nAnyways, 2nd strike is definitely nice to have, but shouldn''t be a deal breaker if you like everything else about the gun, because in all my  fighting pistol training I''ve always been taught to "tap rack bang" after an FTF and not to attempt a second strike. It''s so obvious most people don''t think about it, but ill never forget it after an instructor told me, "once you run out of ammo, or a failure occurs, your gun immediately becomes a brick... then what?". Anyone who intends to use a pistol for self defence needs to regularly practice failure drills at the range.', 1, 0, '24.114.23.28', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
