(360791, 3255, 360782, 'lifebreakking', 8744, '', 1367006669, 'All small moving parts whether gun or machine use engine oil mixed with kerosine in 1:1.5 respectively. the resultant will be neither thick nor thin and also act as anti rusting solution. . . . . WD40 is normally applied on jammed parts/machine like locks or any other. but flammable does not means you fire a shot and it starts burning. Since it is spray so gases are used like air freshener it goes off in air. \nFor barrel what i do is after firing strip the weapon use the same oil and leave it for a while, then use brush rod (since lead and copper deposits in land and grooves of barrel) and at the end pass the bore snake again and again. And right before firing again pass one bore snake (pull through in layman language). \nTry not to rather never fire the weapon with oily barrel bore otherwise it will take hours to wipe out the dirt out of barrels.     \nThat is what i do and never get rust or jammed in my weapons.', 1, 0, '182.189.63.74', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
