(361393, 11372, 361359, '12GAUGE', 608, '', 1367267495, '[QUOTE=Aquarius;361359]Very informative 12GAUGE bro..\r\n\r\n1) So do you mean we should,nt use it in polymer handguns ??\r\n\r\n2) If its not suitable to store it in plastic & wooden containers then how about storing in glass bottles ??\r\n\r\n3) Can it be used to remove superficial rust on a weapon ??[/QUOTE]\r\n\r\n1) Bro, you can only use it to clean metal parts. it is not recommended to clean polymer parts with PG-cleaner as it contains thinner which is mostly acetone which can harm polymer and plastic parts.\r\n\r\n2) yes sir, I always recommend storing PG-cleaner in glass bottles.\r\n\r\n3) In my humble opinion, PG-cleaner is will not remove superficial rust. for that you should give diesel or WD40 a shot.\r\n\r\nRegards.', 1, 1, '39.47.162.168', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
