(362948, 10824, 339492, 'Moeen', 704, '', 1367820530, 'Salam All,\nHere is the deal with the 22 ammo I have experienced, the wax coating in the hot climate tends to weaken if not destroy the powder charge.  Also the 22lr bullet is seated loosely in the case hence moisture tends to get into it reducing shelf life.  I now keep most of my stock of 22 rounds in ziplock bags with the silica pellets.  This is the main reason as to why most 22 rounds fail.  \nAs for .50CAL''s point regarding cheap ammo purchasers, that is very very true.  Most 22 ammo is purchased in bulk and is quite old usually and fresh stock is a little higher in cost with the costliest being CCI here which does work flawlessly.', 1, 1, '115.186.152.197', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
