(364497, 11417, 364151, 'Turumti', 534, '', 1368554849, 'For beginners, mid-powered airguns are the best. They are not as hold sensitive as their more powerful cousins, hence they are more accurate too. Ideally one should start with a sub 12ftlb gun an work on one technique before graduating to a more powerful gun, say a 16ft lb one and then finally onto a 20ftlb plus weapon. Low recoiling guns are a great platform on which one should the learn the basics of hold and trigger squeeze - the two greatest determinants of accuracy in air rifles. \n\nPower is no good if you cannot hit the target.', 1, 0, '182.178.91.71', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
