(364727, 11406, 364721, 'Deathrow', 14869, '', 1368679322, '@ sulzar..... Sure thing bro, Insha Allah we will try to support in whatever way we can. However I would like to comment on something you said.... TT king of all small arms? I don''t think so brother and I don''t think any one on this forum would like to agree upon that...\n\nEven though Insha Allah my next purchase is going to be a TT as well and I am really looking forward to it, it can not be compared to the range of modern hangguns infact even with the other Norinco (Chinese models)\n\nYes, it is a must to have for every handgun enthusiast in some form (Pakistani, Chinese, Russian or Serbian)...\n\nLet me bring a few draw back this pistol has:\n\n1. Bed Sights and can not be upgraded or replaced without major modifications in the entire slide\n2. .30 Cal are known for their extremely high penetration but fairly low on the accuracy\n3. No Manual Safety, drop Safety, Firing pin Safety or Trigger Safety\n4. Triggers vary from piece to piece even with the same manufacturers. Some triggers are crisp, some have too much creep or are too heavy\n5. Limited firepower (7 to 9 rounds depending upon the make you have)\n6. The Finish is not as good\n7. Too much weight', 1, 1, '110.93.196.12', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
