(364860, 11041, 363045, 'SZBR', 15372, '', 1368716290, 'Is Tactical Arms any good?\n\nI went there today and the guy there (Najam) was extremely helpful. \n\nHe gave me a few buying tips that I would like to share (read-verify) from experienced members:\n\n[B]Ammo[/B]\n1) Two types of S&B 9mm ammo is available in Khi, ie, manufactured in 2001 or in 2012; this is denoted by a number such as "01" or "12" on the rim, with the "12" being better and commanding premium of Rs. 4-5/pop\n2) Two types of Chinese 9mm redbox ammo; the one with "311" and "12" (2012 batch) are better and worth Rs. 40/pop, others retail as low as Rs. 34/pop\n\n[B]Handgun[/B]\n1) There are two types of CZ Dutys on offer and there is something wrong with one of them (guessing polymer bulge?); this can be identified using serial #.\n\nThanks for any feedback!', 1, 0, '204.93.60.165', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
