(365761, 11477, 365712, 'AK47', 162, '', 1369077227, 'CF 98/NP 42, preferably the latter one.\n\nReason? Well, you just can''t get better in the 40-60K range. It''s one perfect handgun and an[I] original[/I]. Means, it''s a design for itself and not a copy over. Moreover, it''s an adapted service handgun.\n\nI had one with me for a night recently. My curiosity screwed it up, when I field stripped it beyond normal limits. Means, I was finally having the sear, hammer and all kinds of funny springs  and small thingies in my hands, the gun out of it''s frame, lol!\n\nWorked with it for the whole night, but in vain. Finally handed it over to a gunsmith next morning who fixed everything in less than an hour. Paid him a grand in reward! Hence, be careful in stripping it beyond limits, it''s a complicated piece of craftsmanship. And that''s one of the reasons I fell in love with it. It''s [I]individuality[/I].\n\n\nRegards.', 1, 1, '182.188.164.101', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
